text:
Context: org.apache.batik.svggen.SVGGeneratorContext 

There is a static array decimalFormats[] in SVGGeneratorContext which is set in
an initialisation block which is not static:

protected static DecimalFormat decimalFormats[] = new DecimalFormat[13];

    {
        decimalFormats[0] = new DecimalFormat("#", dsf);

        String format = "#.";
        for (int i=0; i<=12; i++) {
            format += "#";
            decimalFormats[i] = new DecimalFormat(format, dsf);
        }
    }

There is an instance variable decimalFormat which is declared with an initial
value that is derived from the decimalFormats array. 

Therefore, the non-static block that initialises decimalFormats will be called
after decimalFormat has been set, meaning that decimalFormat will be null
(unless and until setPrecision() is called, when decimalFormat is set again).

should be static, else instance variable decimalFormat refererencing
decimalFormats will be null if setPrecision() is not called
